adjectives.description: nautiloid (comparative more nautiloid, superlative most nautiloid)

entries.meaning: (zoology) Resembling a nautilus; pertaining to the subclass Nautiloidea. [from 19th c.]
A mollusc resembling a nautilus; specifically, a cephalopod of the subclass Nautiloidea. [from 18th c.]
examples: Cephalopods have a long fossil record, the earliest certain cephalopod fossils are loosely coiled or straight shelled nautiloids found in the Cambrian of China 515 million years ago.
